**Goal**: Add file size validation in orchestrator for defense in depth security

**Context**: Identified in code review #956 as medium-priority security improvement

**Problem**:
Currently, file size validation occurs only at HTTP layer (PdfEndpoints.cs). Orchestrator has no size limit check, relying on upstream validation. Defense in depth principle recommends validation at multiple layers.

**Security Risk**: 
If HTTP validation is bypassed (misconfiguration, direct service call), orchestrator could process oversized PDFs leading to memory exhaustion.

**Solution**:
Add explicit size check in EnhancedPdfProcessingOrchestrator before loading PDF.

**Implementation**:

```csharp
// EnhancedPdfProcessingOrchestrator.cs:49-67
public async Task<EnhancedExtractionResult> ExtractTextWithFallbackAsync(
    Stream pdfStream,
    bool enableOcrFallback = true,
    CancellationToken ct = default)
{
    var requestId = Guid.NewGuid().ToString();
    var overallStopwatch = Stopwatch.StartNew();

    // NEW: Validate file size before processing (defense in depth)
    var maxSize = _configuration.GetValue<long>(
        "PdfProcessing:MaxFileSizeBytes",
        104857600); // 100 MB default

    if (pdfStream.CanSeek && pdfStream.Length > maxSize)
    {
        _logger.LogWarning(
            "[{RequestId}] PDF size {Size} bytes exceeds maximum {Max} bytes - rejecting",
            requestId, pdfStream.Length, maxSize);

        return EnhancedExtractionResult.CreateFailure(
            $"PDF size ({pdfStream.Length / 1_000_000:F1} MB) exceeds maximum allowed ({maxSize / 1_000_000} MB)");
    }

    _logger.LogInformation(
        "[{RequestId}] Starting 3-stage PDF extraction pipeline (size: {Size} bytes)",
        requestId, pdfStream.CanSeek ? pdfStream.Length : -1);

    // ... rest of pipeline
}
```

**EnhancedExtractionResult.CreateFailure** (static factory method):
```csharp
public static EnhancedExtractionResult CreateFailure(string errorMessage)
{
    return new EnhancedExtractionResult(
        Success: false,
        ExtractedText: string.Empty,
        PageCount: 0,
        CharacterCount: 0,
        OcrTriggered: false,
        Quality: ExtractionQuality.VeryLow,
        StageUsed: 0,
        StageName: "None",
        TotalDurationMs: 0,
        ErrorMessage: errorMessage);
}
```

**Acceptance Criteria**:
- [ ] Size check added at start of ExtractTextWithFallbackAsync
- [ ] Uses PdfProcessing:MaxFileSizeBytes from configuration
- [ ] Returns failure result (not exception) for oversized PDFs
- [ ] Warning level logging for rejected files
- [ ] Unit test: 101 MB PDF rejected (exceeds 100 MB)
- [ ] Unit test: 100 MB PDF accepted (boundary condition)
- [ ] Unit test: Non-seekable stream handled gracefully (size check skipped)
- [ ] Documentation: troubleshooting.md updated with "file too large" error scenario

**Security Benefits**:
- ✅ Defense in depth (validates at orchestrator, not just HTTP)
- ✅ Prevents memory exhaustion from bypassed validation
- ✅ Consistent error handling at service layer
- ✅ Clear audit trail (logged warnings)

**Testing**:
```csharp
[Theory]
[InlineData(50_000_000, true)]   // 50 MB - under limit
[InlineData(100_000_000, true)]  // 100 MB - at limit
[InlineData(101_000_000, false)] // 101 MB - exceeds limit
public async Task ExtractText_FileSizeLimit_ReturnsExpected(long size, bool shouldSucceed)
{
    // Arrange
    var pdf = CreateTestPdf(size);

    // Act
    var result = await _orchestrator.ExtractTextWithFallbackAsync(pdf);

    // Assert
    Assert.Equal(shouldSucceed, result.Success);
    if (!shouldSucceed)
    {
        Assert.Contains("exceeds maximum", result.ErrorMessage);
        Assert.Equal(0, result.StageUsed);
    }
}
```

