**Goal**: Add startup configuration validation for PDF processing settings

**Context**: Identified in code review #956 as high-priority improvement

**Problem**: 
Currently, invalid PDF processing configuration is detected at runtime (when processing fails), not at startup. This causes delayed error detection and poor developer experience.

**Solution**:
Implement `IValidateOptions<PdfProcessingOptions>` to validate configuration on application startup.

**Implementation**:

1. Create `PdfProcessingOptions` strongly-typed config class:
```csharp
public class PdfProcessingOptions
{
    public QualityOptions Quality { get; set; } = new();
    public long MaxFileSizeBytes { get; set; } = 104857600;
    public UnstructuredOptions Unstructured { get; set; } = new();
    public SmolDoclingOptions SmolDocling { get; set; } = new();
}

public class QualityOptions
{
    public double MinimumThreshold { get; set; } = 0.80;
    public double WarningThreshold { get; set; } = 0.70;
    public int MinCharsPerPage { get; set; } = 500;
}
```

2. Create validator:
```csharp
public class PdfProcessingConfigurationValidator : IValidateOptions<PdfProcessingOptions>
{
    public ValidateOptionsResult Validate(string? name, PdfProcessingOptions options)
    {
        if (options.Quality.MinimumThreshold < 0 || options.Quality.MinimumThreshold > 1)
            return ValidateOptionsResult.Fail("Quality.MinimumThreshold must be 0.0-1.0");

        if (options.Quality.MinCharsPerPage < 100)
            return ValidateOptionsResult.Fail("Quality.MinCharsPerPage must be ≥100");

        if (string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(options.Unstructured.ApiUrl))
            return ValidateOptionsResult.Fail("Unstructured.ApiUrl required");

        if (!Uri.TryCreate(options.Unstructured.ApiUrl, UriKind.Absolute, out _))
            return ValidateOptionsResult.Fail("Unstructured.ApiUrl must be valid URL");

        if (options.MaxFileSizeBytes < 1024 || options.MaxFileSizeBytes > 524288000)
            return ValidateOptionsResult.Fail("MaxFileSizeBytes must be 1KB-500MB");

        return ValidateOptionsResult.Success;
    }
}
```

3. Register in DI:
```csharp
// DocumentProcessingServiceExtensions.cs
services.AddOptions<PdfProcessingOptions>()
    .Bind(configuration.GetSection("PdfProcessing"))
    .ValidateOnStart();

services.AddSingleton<IValidateOptions<PdfProcessingOptions>, 
    PdfProcessingConfigurationValidator>();
```

**Acceptance Criteria**:
- [ ] `PdfProcessingOptions` class created with all settings
- [ ] `PdfProcessingConfigurationValidator` implements `IValidateOptions<T>`
- [ ] Validation covers: thresholds (0.0-1.0), URLs (valid format), file sizes (1KB-500MB)
- [ ] Registered in DI with `.ValidateOnStart()`
- [ ] Unit tests for validator (15 test cases: valid, invalid threshold, invalid URL, etc.)
- [ ] Invalid config causes startup failure with clear error message
- [ ] Documentation updated (configuration.md)

**Benefits**:
- Fails fast on startup (vs runtime failures)
- Clear error messages for misconfigurations
- Defense in depth (validates before any PDF processing)
- Prevents production incidents from config typos

**Testing**:
```csharp
[Theory]
[InlineData(-0.1, false)] // Below minimum
[InlineData(0.0, true)]   // Minimum
[InlineData(0.80, true)]  // Valid
[InlineData(1.0, true)]   // Maximum
[InlineData(1.1, false)]  // Above maximum
public void Validate_QualityThreshold_ReturnsExpected(double threshold, bool expectedValid)
{
    var options = new PdfProcessingOptions 
    { 
        Quality = new QualityOptions { MinimumThreshold = threshold } 
    };
    var validator = new PdfProcessingConfigurationValidator();

    var result = validator.Validate(null, options);

    Assert.Equal(expectedValid, result.Succeeded);
}
```

